WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.960 --> 00:00:02.780
Hello, everyone.

2
00:00:05.240 --> 00:00:08.530
So thank you for coming to the Immunotherapy Mechanisms and

3
00:00:08.560 --> 00:00:10.360
Responses Mini Symposium section.

4
00:00:10.780 --> 00:00:14.710
I'm Rob Manguso from MGH and the Broad Institute, and I'm chairing the

5
00:00:14.760 --> 00:00:17.120
session with May Dar from MD Anderson.

6
00:00:18.180 --> 00:00:19.240
Very excited about the session.

7
00:00:20.660 --> 00:00:24.550
I think there's been some really amazing cancer immunology and immunotherapy

8
00:00:24.620 --> 00:00:28.270
work presented at the conference, and as I think most people here can

9
00:00:28.300 --> 00:00:32.119
appreciate, we now are quite sure that immunotherapy is

10
00:00:32.201 --> 00:00:35.660
working for patients with cancer and inducing incredibly

11
00:00:35.720 --> 00:00:37.980
impressive and durable responses in some cases.

12
00:00:38.020 --> 00:00:39.880
And we've moved into a

13
00:00:41.520 --> 00:00:45.460
period of investigation where we're really trying to figure out why it works

14
00:00:45.540 --> 00:00:47.980
and which patients are going to benefit.

15
00:00:48.040 --> 00:00:49.400
And this mechanistic

16
00:00:50.400 --> 00:00:54.280
work can hopefully lead to the development of new, more effective,

17
00:00:54.300 --> 00:00:57.010
and more specific immunotherapies with less toxicity.

18
00:00:58.220 --> 00:01:00.080
So, super excited to hear the talks

19
00:01:01.480 --> 00:01:02.600
today from our speakers.

20
00:01:04.840 --> 00:01:08.260
Just a few quick housekeeping notes about this session.

21
00:01:09.540 --> 00:01:10.920
Each talk is going to be 10 minutes,

22
00:01:11.860 --> 00:01:15.039
with then five minutes for Q&amp;A. Please hold your

23
00:01:15.100 --> 00:01:18.520
questions to the end of each session.

24
00:01:18.550 --> 00:01:19.500
And when you come to the mic,

25
00:01:20.580 --> 00:01:22.240
please introduce yourself

26
